41:19.580 --> 41:21.281
What's the rumpus?

41:21.314 --> 41:24.851
I knew you were trouble
moment I laid eyes on you.

41:33.894 --> 41:35.862
Miss Smutny.

41:35.896 --> 41:37.898
Inside.

41:37.931 --> 41:40.266
Now.

41:51.845 --> 41:54.848
In all my years
of educating colored children,

41:54.881 --> 41:57.083
I never had a U. S. Marshal
come to my office

41:57.117 --> 41:59.252
and ask to talk to a student.

42:01.187 --> 42:03.189
You mind giving us a minute?

42:07.861 --> 42:09.863
(door opens)

42:11.197 --> 42:13.199
(door closes)

42:16.202 --> 42:18.204
I've been thinking about you.

42:19.873 --> 42:21.708
About me?

42:21.742 --> 42:23.877
Mm‐hmm.

42:23.910 --> 42:26.046
Straight A student, I'm told.

42:26.079 --> 42:28.048
Speaks a foreign language.

42:28.081 --> 42:29.750
My Lord.

42:34.087 --> 42:36.723
Your aunt, on the other hand‐‐

42:36.757 --> 42:39.059
she goes on a cough‐syrup bender

42:39.092 --> 42:42.062
that ends in the pistol grip
bludgeoning of a pregnant woman

42:42.095 --> 42:44.731
and the prayerful execution
of her husband.

42:44.765 --> 42:47.067
An armed robbery
that netted Zelmare Roulette

42:47.100 --> 42:49.135
all of $9.58.

42:53.173 --> 42:55.842
You thought she was in jail
for littering?

42:57.678 --> 43:00.647
Oh, and then there's
her paramour Swanee Capps.

43:00.681 --> 43:02.783
She was the third wheel
on a bank robbery crew

43:02.816 --> 43:04.785
that killed
a bank‐manager father‐of‐three

43:04.818 --> 43:06.953
and the coach
of a peewee football team.

43:06.987 --> 43:08.989
This is who you're protecting.

43:11.825 --> 43:13.794
I know they're family,

43:13.827 --> 43:15.962
and I know there,
on the north side of town,

43:15.996 --> 43:18.264
colored folks talk
about "us versus them"

43:18.298 --> 43:20.133
and "we got to stick together"
and what have you.

43:20.166 --> 43:23.069
But if you deem yourself
a civilized person,

43:23.103 --> 43:24.404
and I know you do,

43:24.437 --> 43:27.941
you've got to act
in a civilized manner.

43:27.974 --> 43:30.210
End of story.

43:30.243 --> 43:32.212
So...

43:32.245 --> 43:34.948
I'm asking.

43:34.981 --> 43:37.684
Where's your auntie at?

43:39.820 --> 43:41.788
"Civilized"?

43:41.822 --> 43:43.824
Mm‐hmm. That's what I said.

43:45.258 --> 43:46.727
You know, do you not,
that Africa is

43:46.760 --> 43:48.895
the birthplace of civilization?

43:48.929 --> 43:51.998
Which means both
your ancestors and mine came

43:52.032 --> 43:54.067
from the same green savannah.

43:55.101 --> 43:57.771
I got an "A" in anthropology.

43:57.804 --> 43:59.740
That's factual.

44:04.745 --> 44:06.146
(laughs)

44:08.849 --> 44:10.183
Fascinating.

44:11.852 --> 44:14.154
But...
(laughs)

44:14.187 --> 44:17.691
Listen, I've been mired in
this town going on ten days now,

44:17.724 --> 44:19.159
and I need to get home
to the wife and kids,

44:19.192 --> 44:20.894
so I'll make this simple.

44:20.927 --> 44:23.930
Tell me where your aunt is,
or I'll get you expelled.

44:25.832 --> 44:28.802
‐Sir...
‐Oh, now it's "sir."

44:31.838 --> 44:33.807
‐Please.
‐No.

44:33.840 --> 44:37.143
The Lord said shake the tree,
and I'm shaking it.

44:37.177 --> 44:40.814
Your life or hers.
One of 'em's getting ruined.

44:40.847 --> 44:43.383
Which one is up to you.

44:55.228 --> 44:57.731
Boss, let me explain.

44:57.764 --> 45:00.767
Get him home.
His mama's worried sick.

45:01.802 --> 45:03.203
You can handle that, right?

45:03.236 --> 45:05.872
Of course I can. I didn't even
want to be in there.

45:05.906 --> 45:07.240
Later.

45:15.248 --> 45:16.883
Ready to work?

45:16.917 --> 45:18.885
Yes, sir.

45:18.919 --> 45:20.220
We leave in five.

45:20.253 --> 45:21.922
Arm up.

45:28.161 --> 45:29.830
Calling all cars.

45:29.863 --> 45:32.833
Suspect fugitives are holed up
at the New Parie Hotel.

45:32.866 --> 45:34.768
I am inbound, requesting backup.

45:34.801 --> 45:36.002
DISPATCHER:
Roger that.

45:36.036 --> 45:38.004
(laughs)

45:38.038 --> 45:41.341
I could get used to this.

45:41.374 --> 45:46.012
What, masticating savory vittles
and imbibing top‐shelf hooch?

45:46.046 --> 45:47.347
Hoo‐wee!

45:47.380 --> 45:50.083
Someone's been studying
their vocabulary.

45:50.116 --> 45:53.486
I am trying to be punctilious
with my locution.

45:53.520 --> 45:56.022
Girl, I don't know
what you just said,

45:56.056 --> 45:58.024
but I like the way it sound.

45:58.058 --> 45:59.960
(both laughing)

46:02.596 --> 46:04.130
(Zelmare and Swanee gasp)

46:04.164 --> 46:05.398
OPAL:
Hands.

46:05.431 --> 46:07.501
Ladies.

46:10.003 --> 46:12.072
Cover yourselves up.

46:12.105 --> 46:13.439
Never mind that.

46:13.473 --> 46:15.909
Let's get this over with.

46:15.942 --> 46:17.878
‐LOY: You're the puker?
‐(clicks tongue)

46:17.911 --> 46:19.245
So you must be the shooter.

46:19.279 --> 46:20.947
Give me my gun,
and I'll show you.

46:20.981 --> 46:22.282
LOY:
They got spirit.

46:22.315 --> 46:25.886
God help me,
I love a girl with spirit.

46:25.919 --> 46:27.320
Get dressed.

46:29.289 --> 46:31.457
(tires squealing)

46:31.491 --> 46:33.259
(car door closes)

46:33.293 --> 46:35.128
SWANEE:
Mister,

46:35.161 --> 46:37.230
either rape us
or kill us already.

46:38.398 --> 46:40.867
LOY:
Dying's too easy.

46:40.901 --> 46:43.937
You owe me,
and I'm putting you to work.

46:43.970 --> 46:46.072
‐We ain't whores.
‐Don't need whores.

46:46.106 --> 46:48.308
Need soldiers,
invisible soldiers.

46:48.341 --> 46:51.211
Soldiers the other side
can't see coming.

46:51.244 --> 46:53.614
Who's more invisible than you?

46:53.647 --> 46:55.281
DEAFY:
Which room

46:55.315 --> 46:57.984
are the two jailbirds in‐‐
the Negro and the Injun?

46:58.018 --> 47:00.020
313.

47:02.656 --> 47:04.525
We don't like bosses.

47:05.959 --> 47:08.361
You like bullets?

47:10.096 --> 47:12.098
What do you want us to do?

47:24.945 --> 47:26.212
(car doors close)

47:26.246 --> 47:28.481
(engine starts)

47:28.515 --> 47:29.482
ZELMARE:
Hey...

47:29.516 --> 47:30.651
(continues indistinctly)

47:30.684 --> 47:32.085
(engine starts)

47:32.118 --> 47:34.154
(car door closes)

47:39.425 --> 47:41.427
Son of a biscuit.

47:56.943 --> 47:58.579
Good afternoon.

47:58.612 --> 48:00.614
Afternoon.

48:01.948 --> 48:04.184
Cup of joe, Doc?

48:09.556 --> 48:11.558
Not today, Nadine.

48:30.611 --> 48:32.579
Am I talking to you,

48:32.613 --> 48:35.315
or am I talking to him?

48:35.348 --> 48:37.584
Please. (sniffles)

48:37.618 --> 48:39.419
Have a seat.

48:39.452 --> 48:41.454
Where is the consigliere?

48:43.690 --> 48:45.692
Please.

48:50.997 --> 48:52.999
(Calamita laughs)

48:55.602 --> 48:57.604
You ever...?

49:00.607 --> 49:03.376
You ever see a baby in a box?

49:03.409 --> 49:04.511
What?

49:04.545 --> 49:06.613
A human baby, I'm saying.

49:06.647 --> 49:11.251
Not some‐‐ what do you‐‐
small dog.

49:11.284 --> 49:13.587
A puppy.

49:13.620 --> 49:15.355
They're called puppies.

49:15.388 --> 49:17.624
(laughs)

49:19.793 --> 49:21.995
I know they are called...

49:25.766 --> 49:28.301
Listen, shit for brains,

49:28.334 --> 49:32.138
this... your little powwows

49:32.172 --> 49:34.140
with the consigliere‐‐

49:34.174 --> 49:36.176
that's over.

49:38.111 --> 49:40.246
You're not listening,

49:40.280 --> 49:42.282
so we are gonna stop talking.

49:53.660 --> 49:58.398
Give some indication you
understand the English language.

49:58.431 --> 50:00.233
I thought you said
we weren't talking.

50:00.266 --> 50:02.302
What?

50:09.075 --> 50:12.378
You said you were done talking,

50:12.412 --> 50:14.715
but then you kept on talking.

50:17.150 --> 50:20.086
(Calamita laughing)

50:22.656 --> 50:24.658
CALAMITA:
You think you're so smart?

50:24.691 --> 50:27.327
Let's see how smart...

50:27.360 --> 50:30.463
you are, talking to my knife.

50:33.600 --> 50:35.602
Wait.

50:37.704 --> 50:39.806
Have you seen a baby in a box?

50:39.840 --> 50:42.142
I was...

50:42.175 --> 50:44.511
a baby in a box, cheese dick.

50:46.547 --> 50:50.083
On the boat, coming over.

50:50.116 --> 50:53.787
Just me and Mama‐‐ 15 years old.

50:53.820 --> 50:56.222
And she died, my mama,

50:56.256 --> 50:59.425
coming into New York Harbor.

51:00.727 --> 51:03.597
Tuberculosis, down in the hold.

51:05.699 --> 51:08.669
So then it's just me‐‐
a baby in a box‐‐ which...

51:08.702 --> 51:10.470
Welcome to America.

51:10.504 --> 51:12.706
Everybody's got a sad story.

51:15.308 --> 51:17.343
No, no, no, no.

51:23.216 --> 51:25.218
You're not getting it.

51:27.621 --> 51:30.757
Why I'm telling you
is not feel bad for me.

51:31.858 --> 51:35.228
Why I'm telling you is,

51:35.261 --> 51:38.398
you need to know...

51:38.431 --> 51:42.736
there ain't a monster on Earth

51:42.769 --> 51:45.238
tougher...

51:45.271 --> 51:49.610
than an orphan in a box.

51:49.643 --> 51:52.813
When you're dead in the street
with shit in your pants,

51:52.846 --> 51:56.550
just remember that...

51:56.583 --> 51:59.786
you should've listened.

52:02.889 --> 52:04.858
Is that a fact?

52:04.891 --> 52:07.761
Yes.

52:07.794 --> 52:09.796
That's a fact.

52:10.897 --> 52:13.366
(sniffles)

52:20.306 --> 52:22.576
Nadine.

52:22.609 --> 52:25.445
I think I'll have
that cup of coffee now.

52:28.615 --> 52:32.485
Son, I hate to be the one
to tell you, but...

52:32.519 --> 52:35.155
you got it all wrong.

52:36.823 --> 52:40.594
Your countryman Machiavelli‐‐

52:40.627 --> 52:42.596
he wrote,

52:42.629 --> 52:47.267
"He who wishes to be obeyed
must know how to command."

52:50.804 --> 52:52.806
Thank you, Nadine.

53:04.350 --> 53:06.620
(sighs)

53:17.463 --> 53:21.001
Like I tried to tell you,

53:21.034 --> 53:24.470
I don't know how
they do it in your country,

53:24.505 --> 53:26.873
but here in America...

53:28.875 --> 53:31.411
...respect is earned.

53:34.915 --> 53:37.250
Ebal‐‐

53:37.283 --> 53:39.720
he earned my respect.

53:45.626 --> 53:47.628
But you...

53:49.696 --> 53:51.698
(laughing):
You...

53:54.334 --> 53:57.871
You're just boys...

53:57.904 --> 54:01.041
making a mess

54:01.074 --> 54:04.010
that one day

54:04.044 --> 54:06.246
I'm gonna have to clean up.

54:08.715 --> 54:09.916
Hmm?

54:14.655 --> 54:16.623
Thanks...

54:16.657 --> 54:18.992
for the coffee, Nadine.

54:28.935 --> 54:30.537
(door opens, bell jingles)

54:30.571 --> 54:32.472
(sniffles)

54:34.508 --> 54:36.376
(door closes, bell jingles)

54:46.452 --> 54:48.021
(door opens, bell jingles)

54:48.054 --> 54:50.056
(footfalls approaching)

54:51.658 --> 54:53.660
(door closes)

55:20.687 --> 55:22.723
♪ ♪

55:50.617 --> 55:52.619
♪ ♪

56:07.133 --> 56:09.102
We should blow.

56:09.135 --> 56:11.471
Bulls'll be here soon.

56:11.505 --> 56:14.107
He don't deserve to be left out
in the street like this.

56:14.140 --> 56:16.176
(siren wailing)

56:16.209 --> 56:18.411
(sighs)

56:19.445 --> 56:21.381
Boss, we got to go.

56:24.951 --> 56:27.888
(siren wailing)

56:27.921 --> 56:31.758
Come on. Come on.

56:49.510 --> 56:52.078
(cars departing)

57:02.155 --> 57:04.157
♪ ♪

59:36.743 --> 59:38.111
MAN:
Now I get it.

59:38.144 --> 59:39.713
(rooster crows)
